cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DS, cs.CV 

The paper discusses a new approach for optimizing unknown functions, which is particularly useful for tuning hyperparameters in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also mentions experimental results on both low and high dimensional problems, which suggests that it could be relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CV (Computer Vision).
